<F P=100> Antigua </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Malval Government Members Banned From Leaving </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Malval Government Members Banned From Leaving </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0106175094 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1500 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0106175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government of provisional president attorney 
Emile Jonassaint has officially banned the members of the 
resigning government of Mr. Robert Malval from leaving the 
country. In a communique issued on the night of 30 May, the 
Ministry of the Interior asked the state employees and 
government members not to leave the country before providing 
explanations about their management of the public coffers. A 
formal order has already been applied in that regard at the 
border posts in order to block the travel of the people affected 
by those measures. No reactions to the measures have been 
recorded from the standpoint of the resigning government of 
Robert Malval. The resigning prime minister was supposed to 
leave the country at the beginning of this month in order to 
participate at the OAS General Assembly on 6 June in Belem, 
Brazil. 
  We have learned today from the cabinet of Mr. Malval that he 
had decided not to go to Brazil after all, feeling that after 11 
May 1994 his place is in Haiti along with the Haitian people and 
standing before the usurpers of the legal power -- unquote [no 
opening quote as heard]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

