<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Freezes Malval Government Funds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank Freezes Malval Government Funds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0106173394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1500 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0106173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The central bank, the Bank of the Republic of Haiti, 
has frozen nearly 15 million Haitian dollars belonging to the 
resigning government of Mr. Robert Malval. The funds, which 
have been blocked since the arrival on the scene of the 
provisional government of attorney Jonassaint, are for social 
and humanitarian programs. It should be noted that this money 
was provided by the U.S. Agency for International Development 
[USAID] and was aimed at financing USAID humanitarian projects 
and food and work programs for the impoverished. 

</TEXT>

