<H3> <TI>   Israel's Peres Visits, Meets With Menem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel's Peres Visits, Meets With Menem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0206062294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 2 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0206062294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres spent a lightning, 
four-hour visit in Buenos Aires last night. The foreign 
minister conferred with Argentine President Carlos Menem and 
briefed him about the autonomy agreement with the Palestinians. 
  After the meeting, Minister Peres told reporters that Israel 
has evidence that a foreign country was involved in the 
explosion at the Israeli Embassy in Buenos Aires two years ago. 
He added that Israel will publicize the details after it 
completes its investigation into the incident. Twenty-two 
people were killed and many wounded in the explosion. 
  Minister Peres also denounced the continued presence of Nazi 
criminals in Argentina. 

</TEXT>

