<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Reached With Cuba To Amortize Debt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreement Reached With Cuba To Amortize Debt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0206014394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2221 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0206014394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 1 Jun (EFE) -- Sources at the Cuban 
Embassy in Brasilia have said that Cuba will amortize $38.3 
million of the debt it owes Brazil with medicines for the 
Brazilian public health sector, based on an agreement negotiated 
by the governments of the two countries. 
  The Brazilian and Cuban Governments recently negotiated a 
new 
medicine deal worth $15 million, of which 50 percent will be 
used for amortizing debts. Another $15 million transaction will 
be concluded in the immediate future. 

</TEXT>

