BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic developments monitored through 31 May. 
  Augusto de la Torre, the director of the Central Bank of 
Ecuador, has described the tentative agreement reached with 
foreign banks to renegotiate the country's foreign commercial 
debt as "positive." De la Torre said he hopes other banks will 
soon express their support for this agreement. (Quito Voz de 
los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 26 May 94) 
  Monetary policy chief Ana Lucia Armijo has said that in 
June, 
the Ecuadoran Government will renegotiate its debt with the 
Paris Club. (Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 27 May 
94) 

</TEXT>

