<H3> <TI>   Frei Accepts U.S. Invitation To Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Frei Accepts U.S. Invitation To Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0206034794 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 0100 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0206034794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Eduardo Frei today confirmed that within 
four weeks' time he will travel to Washington at the invitation 
of U.S. President Bill Clinton. 
  It had been rumored in Washington that Clinton was 
interested 
in inviting his Chilean counterpart to a meeting at the White 
House. 
  Today in Santiago, President Frei confirmed the invitation 
to 
visit the United States at the end of the month. 
  [Begin Frei recording] Well, we are awaiting the official 
announcement by the White House and by the Chilean Foreign 
Ministry of a visit to Washington on 28 June, a visit that will 
include a working day with President Clinton at the White House. 
[end recording] 
  In Washington, Patricio Silva, Chilean ambassador to the 
United States, reported that the agenda of the meeting will 
include political issues, but that Chile's overriding interest 
will be the possibility of joining NAFTA. 
  [Begin Silva recording] It is a clear indication of the 
Clinton administration's interest in Latin America--which is 
expressed in this invitation made to the president--and 
especially in Chile. As you very well know, Chile's presence in 
U.S. news, public opinion, and political opinion is quite 
considerable. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

