<DATE1>  1 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Robaina Describes UN as `Intervention Tool' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Robaina Describes UN as `Intervention Tool' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0106221294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0106221294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A call for an immediate cessation of hostilities and 
for preservation of the national unity of Yemen are among the 
most significant issues contained in the draft resolution of the 
11th Ministerial Summit of the Nonaligned Movement. On 31 May, 
experts began to work on the resolution, which will be presented 
for final approval on 3 June. 
  Meanwhile, the heads of the delegations are meeting behind 
closed doors in what the organizers are calling a brainstorm, 
which will last into the night. In the morning, Robaina is 
expected to give an address on the democratization of 
international relations. Since the beginning of the summit, 
numerous delegations have defended the need for radical 
transformation of the UN Security Council and increased openness 
in its proceedings+. 
  In an address before the plenum on 31 May, Robaina issued a 
call to thwart efforts to turn the United Nations into an 
intervention tool against underdeveloped nations. Robaina has 
also conducted an intensive exchange of opinions with foreign 
ministers from diverse countries. Robaina will meet today with 
representatives from Kenya, Belize, South Africa, Palestine, 
Algeria, and Qatar. 

</TEXT>

