  [Text] Havana, 1 Jun (PL) -- Honduran Foreign Minister 
Ernesto Paz Aguilar will visit Cuba at the invitation of the 
Foreign Ministry. An authorized Cuban Foreign Ministry source 
confirmed Paz Aguilar's trip to PRENSA LATINA today. The date 
for the trip will be coordinated by the two countries soon. 
  The Honduran foreign minister met with Roberto Robaina, his 
Cuban counterpart, in Cairo, taking advantage of their 
participation in the meeting of foreign ministers of the 
Nonaligned Movement which is being held in the Egyptian capital. 
  On this occasion, he asked Robaina to convey greetings from 
Honduran President Carlos Roberto Reina to Cuban President Fidel 
Castro and referred to the possibility of a meeting between the 
two chiefs of state during the upcoming Fourth Ibero-American 
Summit to be held in Cartagena de Indias. 
  Cuba and Honduras do not have diplomatic relations. 
Diplomatic ties were suspended by the Honduran Government in 
April 1961 following an OAS agreement. 

