<H3> <TI>   GRANMA Article Responds to Clinton Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GRANMA Article Responds to Clinton Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0206211694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0206211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 2 June, GRANMA published an article by reporter 
Luis Vaies Delgado entitled Public Letter to a President, in 
which he responds to William Clinton's message of 20 May, 
supposedly for the people of Cuba. 
  If we have gotten to where we are now and we are still here, 
it is because we have learned never to make the slightest 
compromise regarding sovereignty and independence. Vaies points 
out that 20 May 1902 is not Cuban Independence Day; it is the 
day that the crime of seizing the independence that the Cuban 
people had fought for for over a third of a century 
pseudojudicially took place. He adds further on in the article: 
We arrived at 20 May 1902 through the cunning and greed of a 
nation that coveted Cuba for a century. After analyzing a number 
of historic events that prove this, Luis Vais responds, clearly 
and precisely, to several of the U.S. President's statements 
regarding our people and his government. In this manner, the 
deceit in those statements is exposed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

