<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   May Ends With Sugarcane Planting Behind Schedule </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    May Ends With Sugarcane Planting Behind Schedule </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0306020594 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 0133 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0306020594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After surpassing the sugarcane spring planting 
program in April, the Sugar Industry Ministry was behind 
schedule at the end of May. Preliminary data shows that 8,700 
caballerias have been planted; this represents a lag of over 
5,000 caballerias, according to May projections. The excessive, 
continuous rains in the eastern provinces and the ensuing floods 
are among the causes for the delay. We must keep in mind that 
the sugarcane planting program is of national significance in 
Camaguey, Holguin, Las Tunas, Granma, and Santiago de Cuba 
Provinces. It is expected that the lost time will be recovered 
in June through tremendous planting efforts. Everything will 
mainly depend, however, upon the amount of land prepared to 
receive the seed. 

</TEXT>

