<H3> <TI>   Robaina Stresses Importance of Ibero-American Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Robaina Stresses Importance of Ibero-American Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0306000594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0306000594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina </F>
in Cairo, Egypt, by Roberto Gili in Havana -- live or recorded] 
  [Text] [Gili] We would like to know what the Cuban 
delegation to the Ibero-American Summit -- to be held on 14-15 
June in Cartagena de Indias, Colombia -- expects to achieve. 
  [Robaina] These summits continue to be special occasions 
when 
we can meet without being ordered to do so by the Empire. The 
Ibero-American Summit, specifically, is already threatened by 
the Miami hemispheric summit, convened by the U.S. Government 
for the clear purpose of discrediting it. I believe that in 
light of such a maneuver, it is important for the Cartagena 
summit to be stronger than ever in terms of its development. 
  I have no doubt that, independent of their efforts, the 
Latin 
American peoples are increasingly more independent and will 
continue to find their own path. We need to see how the rest of 
America responds, but I have confidence in Colombia's readiness 
and the peoples' response. I believe this will be an important 
forum for discussion and that Colombia would like it to become a 
stage for debate, discussion, and unrehearsed speeches. I hope 
it will be a summit for action rather than intentions. 
  [Gili] Thank you minister. 

</TEXT>

