<H3> <TI>   Meets Guyanese Delegate, Egyptian Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets Guyanese Delegate, Egyptian Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0306004494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0306004494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Froilan Arencibia from Cairo, Egypt] </F>
  [Excepts] Participants in the 11th Ministerial Summit of 
the Nonaligned Movement [NAM] have enthusiastically welcomed the 
Latin American group's decision to nominate Colombia as host 
country for the upcoming heads of state summit. The nomination 
will be made official tomorrow during the closing session of the 
summit. It is expected to be easily approved. The news was also 
enthusiastically received by the members of the Cuban delegation 
who volunteered to cooperate with Colombia. 
  In this regard, Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina affirmed 
that he trusts Colombia will contribute to the unity of the NAM 
and to revitalizing its role in the international arena. 
[passage omitted] 
  Robaina continued his program of interviews, which today 
included the representative from Guyana and Egyptian Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Mahmud Musa. Robaina and Musa discussed ways to 
find common ground in the economic sphere and conducted an 
exchange of opinions on the NAM summit. Musa invited Robaina to 
conduct an official visit to Egypt and Robaina likewise invited 
Musa to visit Cuba. 
  Later in the evening, Robaina met with businessmen, briefing 
them on the characteristics of Cuban economic policies. 

</TEXT>

