  [Excerpts] Iran's Minister of Construction Jihad Gholam 
Reza Foruzesh arrived in Havana accompanied by an ample 
delegation, made up of vice ministers and government authorities. 
  Foruzesh stated that relations between Cuba and Iran are 
very 
good and the purpose of his visit is to strengthen them even 
more. His visit will also cover the analysis of new areas of 
cooperation between both nations primarily in the areas of 
technology and fishing. Foruzesh will analyze, together with 
Cuban authorities, the paths for broadening trade and economic 
relations in a short period of time with Cuba . 
  The delegation will cover a tight agenda during their visit 
to Cuba, from which new projects could develop. [passage omitted] 
  [Begin Foruzesh recording in Persian with passage by passage 
translation into Spanish] There are very good relations, 
especially diplomatic ones, between Cuba and Iran. We have come 
to analyze new areas of cooperation between both nations, 
primarily in the areas of technology and fishing, as well as to 
study new paths for broadening trade and economic relations. I 
see this future cooperation as a clear and positive. [end 
recording] 
  Minister of Foreign Trade Ricardo Cabrisas and Jose M. 
Miyar, 
both members of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of 
Cuba, greeted the Iranian delegation upon their arrival. 

