<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Tuesday, thousands of Tlaxcalan residents took to 
the streets to demand the resignation of Governor Jose Antonio 
Alvarez Lima. Dissident teachers of sections 31 and 35 of the 
Trade Union of Education Workers [SNTE] seized the Government 
Palace and kidnapped local Government Director Jose Luis 
Arhuijo. The teachers demand solutions to their salary-increase 
demands. Most businesses are closed and government offices and 
banks have closed. 

