<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Diego Fernandez de Cevallos, National Action Party 
[PAN] presidential candidate, has reiterated to the media what 
he has been saying all along: he will not participate in the 
debate among all the presidential candidates. On 28 and 29 May, 
he said the following: 
  [Begin Fernandez recording] I believe that if there is time 
for multiple debates, it makes no sense for all of us to meet on 
the same day and at the same time, especially when the objective 
of the debate has already been expressed. I repeat, I think 
there is enough time; it makes no sense for us to meet at the 
same time and place. [end recording] 

