<H3> <TI>   President Endara Requests Reentry Into Rio Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Endara Requests Reentry Into Rio Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0306040594 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0306040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Guillermo Endara has asked the members of 
the Rio Group to accept Panama's full reincorporation into the 
forum, which expelled Panama during the former regime of Manuel 
Antonio Noriega. 
  Endara explained that the conditions that led to Panama's 
expulsion are a thing of the past and that the country now is 
involved in a democratic process that became stronger with the 8 
May general elections -- elections in which opposition candidate 
Ernesto Perez Balladares was elected. 
  Endara's petition was expressed in a letter he sent to the 
Rio Group. In the letter, Endara stressed: I feel an era is 
ending with this last diplomatic effort I am making today. With 
your support, my country and people will again occupy a place of 
honor which, because of a lack of democracy, was suddenly 
snatched away from them, and which now, thank God, is being 
returned. 

</TEXT>

