<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Hints at Future Menem-Duhalde Ticket </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Hints at Future Menem-Duhalde Ticket </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0206191294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1123 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0206191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 2 Jun (NA) -- "Boys, the formula 
returns." With an expansive smile and this remark, which may be 
an indication, President Carlos Menem on 1 June received the 
photographers and cameramen that recorded the meeting he had 
with Buenos Aires Province Governor Eduardo Duhalde at 
Government House. 
  Flanked by [Presidency] Secretary General Eduardo Bauza and 
Buenos Aires Province Deputy Governor Rafael "Balito" Roma, 
Menem and Duhalde waited standing up in the presidential office 
for the cameras and television crews to enter. 
  As though he wanted to demonstrate that his spats with 
Duhalde are pure fantasy, Menem was openly at ease and was even 
heard to talk with the governor about Argentina's win over 
Israel [in a 31 May soccer match]. 
  With a conspirator's smile, Menem then faced photographers 
and cameramen, to whom he said: "Boys, the formula once again," 
referring to the possibility of repeating the two-man [ticket] 
that led the Justicialist Party to victory on 14 May 1989. 
  Duhalde could do no less than smile at the quip made by 
Menem, who, behind the scenes, once again began to pull the 
governor's leg regarding the size of his head: "He always 
overshadows me." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

