BFN 

  [Excerpt] Santa Fe, 1 Jun (NA) -- The National Constituent 
Assembly resumed sessions today. It continued discussing the 
rules and regulations that will govern the Constituent Assembly 
sessions. Neuquen Grand Front Jaime De Nevares has resigned as a 
constituent assembly member. 
  The Neuquen bishop emeritus supported his resignation, 
claiming that the Constituent Assembly "is completely null and 
void," adding that the Constituent Assembly is "a farce." 
  With De Nevares' departure, the Grand Front loses a seat 
because vacant seats are not replaced after members have taken 
the oath. [passage omitted] 

