<H3> <TI>   Tucuman Province Reports Monthly Deficit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tucuman Province Reports Monthly Deficit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0206190094 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2107 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0206190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Buenos Aires, 1 Jun (NA) -- Tucuman Governor 
Ramon "Palito" Ortega admitted today that his province has a 
monthly deficit of 6.5 million pesos. He blames this situation 
on the signing of the Fiscal Pact with the federal government 
and on the transfer of federal schools to the provincial 
government. 
  Ortega indicated that his province has a "deficit" because 
of 
"the non-collection of revenues following the signing of the 
Fiscal Pact, which caused a social security deficit of 3.5 
million pesos." 
  The governor also blamed the situation on the transfer of 
federal schools to the provincial government and on salary 
increases for teachers. He emphasized that the latter measures 
increased the monthly deficit to 6.5 million pesos. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

