<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0206235294 </F>
<F P=103> PY0206235294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Argentina monitored through 2 
June. 
  Media Secretary Raul Burzaco reported that Economy Minister 
Domingo Cavallo today informed the cabinet that the total 
provincial deficit stands at $1.3 billion, of which $500 million 
involves the northwestern provinces. (Buenos Aires Radio 
Nacional Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 27 May 94) 
  It was reported that the unemployment rate hit 12 percent at 
the end of April 1994, or an increase of 2.7 percent in the past 
six months. In October 1993 the unemployment rate stood at 9.3 
percent. Industrial circles blamed the increase on foreign 
competition, increasing internal costs, and the incorporation of 
new machinery and technologies that replace labor. (Buenos 
Aires LA PRENSA in Spanish 1 Jun 94 Economic Section p 5) 

</TEXT>

