<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0206235894 </F>
<F P=103> PY0206235894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Peru monitored through 2 June. 
  The Peruvian Government received $1.361 billion as a result 
of the auction of the Peruvian Telephone Company, and the sale 
of 35 percent of the shares of the National Telecommunications 
Enterprise of Peru. (Lima LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 18 May 94 
Economic Section p 11) 
  The National Statistics Institute on 1 June reported that 
Peru's industrial installed capacity increased 10 percent from 
May 1993 to 31 April. The total use of industrial companies' 
installed capacity rose to 56 percent. The cement and metal 
industries registered the greatest increases, with 90 percent 
and 83 percent respectively. The private Apoyo Inc. consulting 
firm reported that the average usage rate of the industrial 
installed capacity ranges from 60 to 70 percent. (Madrid EFE in 
Spanish 1908 GMT 1 Jun 94) 

</TEXT>

