<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Red Sun' Guerrillas To Lay Down Arms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Red Sun' Guerrillas To Lay Down Arms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0306031394 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 2 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0306031394 </F>
<F P=104>  Quito Voz de los Andes </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister General Jose Gallardo has announced 
that Red Sun--Puka Inti, in Quechua--an Ecuadoran terrorist 
group similar to Peru's Shining Path Maoist movement, will 
surrender its weapons. This evening we will have very pleasant 
news for the Ecuadoran people, Gallardo said, although he would 
not provide details. 
  Red Sun began operating about three years ago and carried 
out 
dynamite attacks on public installations and on the headquarters 
of political parties. None of those attacks produced casualties. 
  [Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish at 2105 GMT on 2 June, in a 
similar 150-word, Quito-datelined report, adds: "Gallardo 
reported that the subversive Ecuadoran group will surrender its 
weapons to military authorities within the next few hours and 
that its members will join the legal democratic process."] 

</TEXT>

