<F P=102>   PA0206162594 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1531 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0206162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 2 Jun (EFE) -- Three of the Cubans who broke 
into the Belgian Embassy in Havana last Saturday left the 
building last night, according to official sources. The sources 
did not give the identity of the people who left the embassy 
last night, nor the identity of the person who left Sunday night. 
  Observers believe the four who left the residence of the 
Belgian ambassador could be the last people who were 
unexplainably able to break through dozens of police on Saturday 
morning. In documents released to the media on Tuesday, the 
refugees expressed their suspicions that the four were State 
Security agents. 

</TEXT>

