<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Following a meeting with President Carlos Salinas de 
Gortari, the citizens' commission to help in investigating Luis 
Donaldo Colosio's homicide has declined the chief of state's 
invitation. This statement was made after members of the 
commission submitted their written resignation to the president. 
They believe their work is unnecessary in view of the 
investigations being conducted by Special Assistant Prosecutor 
Miguel Montes. 
  The citizens' commission told President Salinas that all the 
members agree the commission must be independent. The only 
legal procedure that could give legitimacy to the citizens' 
commission is if Mrs. Diana Laura Riojas [Colosio's widow] 
appoints them as assistants of the public prosecutor's office 
and judicial authorities. 

