BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Paraguay monitored through 2 
June. 
  Yesterday, Presidential spokesman Guillermo Yalik told 
reporters that the inflation rate in May was 0.5 percent. Total 
inflation for the year now stands at 9.8 percent. (Asuncion ABC 
COLOR in Spanish 31 May 94 p 13) 
  The Central Bank reports that total international reserves 
at 
the end of May stand at $901 million, and that the average 
interest the bank receives for its deposits is 3.8 percent. 
(Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 31 May 94 p 13) 

