<H3> <TI>   Attempts To Trespass Mexican, French Embassies Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attempts To Trespass Mexican, French Embassies Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0306192094 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1828 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0306192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 3 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Attempts to trespass the 
residences of the Mexican and French ambassadors and other 
reports of similar actions followed the occupation of the 
Belgian ambassador's home, which is on its seventh day today. 
  Three Cubans unsuccessfully tried to break into Mexican 
Ambassador Carlos Tello Macias' residence located in the 
exclusive neighborhood of Miramar on Monday afternoon, according 
unofficial reports. 
  A similar incident took place on Tuesday when four other 
Cubans tried to break into French Ambassador Jean Raphael 
Dufour's residence, also located in Miramar, which is west of 
Havana. In that incident, security guards arrested two men and 
two others fled. 
  Reports that were later denied of similar incidents in at 
least four other missions circulated in newspapers this week 
while the residence of the Belgian ambassador, Paul Vermiersch, 
continues to be occupied by over 100 Cubans who are trying to 
leave the country. 
  The building is surrounded by police while the authorities 
of 
both governments are holding talks to achieve a peaceful 
evacuation of the house in exchange for a Cuban offer to refrain 
from carrying out any reprisals against the asylum seekers. 

</TEXT>

