<F P=102>   94P20834A </F>
<F P=103> 94P20834A </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Santa Cruz EL MUNDO in Spanish on 2 May 
94 on page 3 reports that Cuba is strengthening scientific and 
cultural ties with Bolivia through university programs and 
tourism. Dr. Jesus Castro, international relations director of 
the Jose Antonio Echeverria Politechnic Institute, said the 
Ideal Tours Agency of La Paz is opening an agency in Santa Cruz 
which will promote tours to Havana. He also announced that 
professors from universities in Havana will be teaching summer 
courses in humanities, technical sciences, and medicine at 
Bolivian universities. 

