<F P=106> [From the "Exclusive" program] </F>
  [Text] Rosa Elena Simeon Negrin, minister of science, 
technology, and the environment, has said that one of the huge 
problems that Latin America faces in competing in world markets 
is a lack of scientists. Simeon pointed out in a PRENSA LATINA 
interview that with the GATT agreements and free trade, most 
products of most Latin American countries are not competitive. 
Simon added: To be able to compete, there must be scientific 
and technological support, which Latin America does not have. 
She went on to say that was the issue that dominated three days 
of debates on scientific development during the meeting of 
scientific, technological, and investigative officials in 
Cartagena de Indias, Colombia. The meeting ended on 3 June with 
a number of recommendations to the Ibero-American heads of state 
and government. 

</TEXT>

