<H3> <TI>   Alarcon, Officials Attend Granma Goverment Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alarcon, Officials Attend Granma Goverment Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0606020694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0606020694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ricardo Alarcon de Quesada, president of the 
National Assembly of the People's Government [ANPP], is 
attending the fourth special session of the provincial People's 
Government in the City of Bayamo. The main goal of the meeting 
is to discuss and approve the progress report which Granma 
Province will render to the ANPP session in July. It was 
ratified at the meeting that the document will be enriched by 
the people in meetings to be held in every district in the 
province. Granma's progress report includes a broad overview of 
the work conducted between 1985 and 1989, as well as the intense 
and productive effort of the entire population between 1990 and 
1994, years within the special period marked by a great spirit 
of sacrifice and commitment to solve the problems created by 
acute material shortages. 
  Granma's delegates and deputies stressed that the food 
program is in need of joint efforts, to increase the seed banks, 
the organic planters, and to use the scientific potential to 
quickly satisfy the people's food needs in a controlled and 
intelligent manner. 
  The fourth special session of Granma's government is also 
being attended by Commander of the Revolution Guillermo Garcia 
Frias; Adolfo Diaz, vice president of the Council of Ministers; 
and Alfredo Enriquez Pina, first secretary of the Communist 
Party of Cuba [PCC] in Granma. The session also discussed the 
proposed shield of the province in which the principal and most 
significant elements of the glorious historic and revolutionary 
endeavors of the province are represented. 

</TEXT>

