<H3> <TI>   Cienfuegos Authorities Prosecute 9 Money Hoarders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cienfuegos Authorities Prosecute 9 Money Hoarders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0306224494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0306224494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The implementation of revolutionary measures against 
the so-called money hoarders continues nationwide. On 3 June, 
the 5 DE SEPTIEMBRE weekly of Cienfuegos carried an article, 
entitled, Act of Justice, regarding the first nine cases being 
processed by the prosecutor's office and other entities in 
accordance with Decree Law 149. Cienfuegos authorities have 
seized from these people who attained their wealth illegally 19 
cars of diverse makes, including two Moscovits, two Ladas, and 
three Jeeps, as well as six motorcycles. Authorities also seized 
13 houses and [passage indistinct] of rice and 2,595 of beans. 
The article adds that the vehicles seized from the money 
hoarders will probably be allocated for use as ambulances and 
for other social services. The 13 homes will be used as schools 
and daycare centers among other uses, and the seized food will 
be distributed to hospitals. 

</TEXT>

