<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Matanzas Authorities Implement Anticrime Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Matanzas Authorities Implement Anticrime Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0306190394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0306190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Implementation of Decree-Law 149 gains momentum in 
Matanzas Province with the start of legal proceedings in seven 
cases of ill-gotten wealth, thanks to the work of the Unified 
Vigilance and Protection System in each municipality. 
Authorities are holding, among other things: six automobiles; 
one truck; one farm; one home; dozens of head of cattle, sheep, 
and pigs; and a great number of domestic appliances. The active 
response to this law, which this operation requires, relies on 
the people's support. The Committees for the Defense of the 
Revolution, the attorney's office, the Interior Ministry 
organizations, and the Finance and Prices Ministry, in 
coordination with other entities, have joined to conduct a 
process whose last step will be the total confiscation of 
ill-gotten goods. Decree-Law 149 is supported by Articles 61 
and 62 of the Constitution, which condemn obtaining wealth 
illegally and which mars the fairness of our socialist society 
and reflects the need to strengthen control on state resources, 
as well as complying effectively with our laws. 

</TEXT>

