<H3> <TI>   Electric Union Announces Continued Power Outages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electric Union Announces Continued Power Outages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0406014394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0406014394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The current electricity generation deficit will 
continue into next week. The outages will therefore follow a 
pattern similar to what has happened lately. The Electric Union 
made this announcement this evening. This entity of the Basic 
Industry Ministry added that the situation in June is not as 
critical as during April and confirmed that Cuba continues to 
receive the necessary spare parts and equipment to conduct 
projected maintenance programs. 
  From 2-8 June, the average power output projected is 1,420 
megawatts and the projected demand will peak at times at 1,835 
megawatts. In other words, there will be deficit similar to that 
experienced in the last few weeks. 
  The Electric Union also announced that a light maintenance 
program is scheduled to be conducted on unit No. 4 of the Carlos 
Manuel de Cespedes Electric Plant in Cienfuegos. This is one of 
the two 150-megawatt generators this plant has under repair. The 
repairs are expected to take four days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-33285 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat108_a_94029" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-108 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

