  [Text] The Moncada II-94 exercise has showcased the high 
level of readiness of unit commands and defense councils of 
Guantanamo Province to confront and repel any aggression. It 
could not be any different. Even though this is a period of 
relative calm, the enemy is combat-ready on the other side of 
the fence. The people of Guantanamo cannot forget that sad 
privilege. 
  The exercise allowed command posts and defense councils to 
demonstrate their skills in command and cooperation, as well as 
in directing operations, and the fight. 
