defense council, affirmed that Moncada II-94 was more than a 
defense exercise; it also contributed to accelerating the work 
being done to repair the damage caused by the recent rains and 
the efforts to build over 500 homes for the people affected, 
marked the restart of the sugar harvest, and highlighted efforts 
to restore the provincial road infrastructure, for which heavy 
earth moving equipment is needed to speed up reconstruction of 
bridges and sewers. 

