<H3> <TI>   Mulino Requests Panama To Be Sight of NAM Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mulino Requests Panama To Be Sight of NAM Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0406195594 Panama City LA PRENSA in Spanish 3 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PA0406195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA PRENSA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Jose Otero] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Jose Mulino requested yesterday the 
support of countries in the Nonaligned Movement (NAM) for Panama 
to be given the seat of the next NAM heads of state summit in 
1999, to "show to the world the country that is to manage the 
Canal in the next century." 
  Mulino made this request during his main speech before the 
11th NAM Foreign Relations Ministers meeting currently being 
held in Cairo, Egypt. 
  "I hope my successors at the foreign ministry will support 
and honor Panama's request to be the seat of the NAM heads of 
state summit in 1999," Mulino emphasized. 
  The foreign minister added in his speech that, if this 
request is granted, Panama will secure its most important 
commitment to the world. 
  Mulino called on all NAM member countries to prepare and 
back 
the initiative unanimously as a homage to the Panamanian people. 
  "We advance, without having any time to loose or any margin 
for errors, toward the historic commitment of receiving the 
Panama Canal on 31 December 1999," Mulino added. 

</TEXT>

