<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Temporary Real-Dollar Parity Announced, Effective 1 July </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Temporary Real-Dollar Parity Announced, Effective 1 July </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0306193694 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 2 
Jun 94 Section 1 p 10 </F>

<F P=103> PY0306193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brasilia -- Finance Minister Rubens Ricupero said 
yesterday that as of 1 July -- when the real will replace the 
real cruzeiro as legal tender -- and for an unspecified time, 
one real will be worth one dollar. 
  The issuance of the real will be backed by part of the 
Brazilian exchange reserves, which currently stand at $38 
billion, considering the concept of international liquidity 
(which includes both available and applied resources). 
  The opening of checking accounts in dollars will not be 
permitted and the current rules governing the exchange of 
foreign currency will be maintained. Thus, there will be no 
free convertibility of the real. 
  Ricupero stated that the real will be backed only by 
exchange 
reserves, consisting of foreign currency and gold. Stocks of 
state-owned companies will not be used to back the issuance of 
the real. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

